Thank you for choosing Microsoft!

This is an agreement between you and Microsoft Corporation that describes your rights to use the Power BI preview software and service (the 'Service'). When using the Service, you must abide by these terms ('this Agreement'). Please also note that in order to use this Service, you need to be located in the United States.

You may sign up for a Microsoft organizational account with an email address provided by your organization (e.g., your employer or educational institution). Please be advised that if you sign up and use the Service with an organizational account (e.g., your work email), the owner of the organizational domain (e.g., your employer or educational institution) may subsequently be able to assume control of your account and obtain access to your data and prior network activities.

For your convenience, we have phrased some of the terms of this Agreement in a question and answer format. You should read the entire Agreement because all of the terms are important and together create a legal agreement that, once accepted by you, applies to you.

  1. Acceptance and changes to agreement
    1. How do I accept this agreement? By using or accessing the Service, or by agreeing to these terms where the option is made available to you in the user interface, you agree to abide by this Agreement without modification by you. If you don't agree, you may not use the Service.
    2. Can Microsoft change this Agreement after I've accepted it? Yes. From time to time, Microsoft may change or amend these terms. If we do, we'll notify you, either through the user interface, in an email message, or through other reasonable means. If you use the Service after the date the change becomes effective, you consent to the changed terms. If you don't agree to the changes, you must stop using the Service. Otherwise, the new terms will apply to you.
    3. What types of changes can I expect to the Service? We continuously work to improve the Service and may change the Service at any time. Since the Service is preview in nature, it may not work correctly or in the same way the final version may work. From time to time we may stop providing portions of the Service. We may do so, for example, if it's no longer feasible for us to provide a Service, the technology advances, customer feedback indicates a change is needed, our agreements with third parties no longer permit us to make their material available, or external issues arise that make it imprudent or impractical to continue.
    4. What about feedback? How will my feedback be used? By agreeing to use the Service you agree to provide feedback to Microsoft. You license to Microsoft without charge all intellectual property or other rights necessary for Microsoft to use, share, and commercialize in any way or for any purpose any feedback. You also license to all third parties without charge all intellectual property or other rights necessary for their products, technologies and services to use or interface with any specific parts of a Microsoft software or service that includes the feedback. You will not give feedback that is subject to any license that requires Microsoft to license its software or documentation or services to third parties because we include our feedback in them. The rights granted in this paragraph are perpetual and world-wide and survive the termination or expiration of this Agreement.

The Service enables you to communicate with others and share or store various types of files, such as photos, documents, music and video. The contents of your communications and your files are your 'Content' and, except for material that we license to you that may be incorporated into your own Content (such as clip art), we don't claim ownership of the Content you provide on the Service. You are responsible for your Content.

      If the owner of your organizational domain has assumed control of your account, please contact your administrator to understand your rights to your Content.

If you don't want others to have that ability, don't use the Service to share your Content. Additionally, if the owner of your organizational domain has assumed control of your account, your administrator will have access to your Content.

      You represent and warrant that for the duration of this Agreement you have (and will have) all the rights necessary for the Content you upload or share on the Service and that the use of the Content, as contemplated in this section 2.2, won't violate any law.

    3. What does Microsoft do with my Content? When you transmit or upload Content to the Service, you're giving Microsoft the worldwide right, without charge, to use Content as necessary: to provide the Service to you, and to improve Microsoft products and services. Microsoft uses and protects your Content as outlined in the privacy statement referenced in section 4.
    4. What type of Content or actions aren't permitted? In order to protect our customers and the Service, we have established this Code of Conduct governing the use of the Service. Content or actions that violate this Agreement aren't permitted.
      1. Don't use the Service to do anything illegal.
      2. Don't engage in any activity that exploits, harms, or threatens to harm children.
      3. Don't send spam or use your account to help others send spam. Spam is unsolicited bulk email, postings or instant messages.
      4. Don't display inappropriate images (e.g. nudity, bestiality, pornography).
      5. Don't engage in activity that is false or misleading (e.g. attempts to ask for money under false pretenses, impersonating someone else).
      6. Don't engage in activity that is harmful to the Service or others (e.g. viruses, stalking, hate speech, advocating violence against others).
      7. Don't infringe upon the rights of others (e.g. unauthorized sharing of copyrighted music, resale or other distribution of Bing maps, photographs and other Content).
      8. Don't engage in activity that violates the privacy of others.
      9. Don't use the Service in any manner that could interfere with, disrupt, negatively affect or inhibit other users from fully enjoying the Service, or that could damage, disable, overburden or impair the functioning of the Service in any manner.
      10. Don't send any unsolicited or unauthorized advertising, solicitations, promotional materials, spam, junk mail, chain letters or pyramid schemes, or conceal or misrepresent the identity of senders of emails, for the purpose of sending spam or other commercial messages.
      11. Don't harvest or collect information about other users, including their email addresses, without their consent.
      12. Don't use any robot, spider, crawler, scraper or other automated means or interface not provided by us to access the Service or to extract data.
      13. Don't reverse engineer any aspect of the Service or do anything that might discover source code or bypass or circumvent measures employed to prevent or limit access to any area, content or code of the Service (except as otherwise expressly permitted by law).
      14. Don't use or attempt to use any account you are not authorized to use.

When investigating these matters, Microsoft or its agents will review Content in order to resolve the issue. This is in addition to the uses we describe in this Agreement and the Privacy Statements.
